Meta Privacy Policy - How Meta collects and uses user data                                             9/17/23, 9:02 PM




                        How do we use your information?




                     20


                     Information about our Products’ performance on your
                     device
                     We collect device information to prevent, diagnose, troubleshoot and fix errors
                     and bugs. This includes how long the app was running, what model of device
                     you were using and other performance and diagnostic information.



                     21


                     Information from cookies and similar technologies
                     Cookies are small pieces of text used to store information on web browsers.
                     We use cookies and similar technologies, including data that we store on your
                     web browser or device, identifiers associated with your device and other
                     software, Social Plugins and the Meta Pixel. They help us provide, protect and
                     improve our Products, such as by personalizing content, tailoring and
                     measuring ads and providing a safer experience.

                     We collect information from cookies stored on your device, including cookie IDs
                     and settings.

                     Read our cookie policies:

                          Meta Cookies Policy

                          Instagram Cookies Policy



